Key Match Events: Iceland scored their first goal in the 39th minute through Orri Óskarsson.
Iceland extended their lead with a second goal in the 58th minute by Jon Dagur Thorsteinsson.
Montenegro's Vladimir Jovovic received a yellow card late in the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Laugardalsvöllur in Reykjavik, Iceland, in front of 4,683 fans.
Others: Montenegro had possession of 58.7% compared to Iceland's 41.3%
Iceland made several substitutions including Patrik Gunnarsson and Arnór Traustason.
